  "script": "I always mocked the tales about the timekeeper’s watch—how it halts before a death. Then, I cleaned my grandfather’s brass pocket watch, frozen at 9:17. At the bus stop, it suddenly ticked in my hand, glass fogged. A whisper: “Sprout.” His private nickname. He died December 17th, 9:17 AM. I Googled the legend; every article vanished. Now, it ticks nightly at 3 AM. My neighbor passed yesterday at 3:05. Is the watch counting down to mine?",
